00:11:35,716 --> 00:11:36,957
data-informed.

272
00:11:37,537 --> 00:11:39,699
When you are data-driven, you might have the tendency

273
00:11:39,839 --> 00:11:42,981
to focus on decisions that will enforce,

274
00:11:43,021 --> 00:11:45,482
like for example, the perfect balancing.

275
00:11:45,522 --> 00:11:49,584
So stall and simplify your design in order

276
00:11:49,624 --> 00:11:50,805
to achieve this perfect balancing.

277
00:11:51,205 --> 00:11:52,527
Let me give you an example.

278
00:11:53,048 --> 00:11:54,830
Imagine this system being your game.

279
00:11:55,311 --> 00:11:57,273
So you have three marble and one plate.

280
00:11:57,774 --> 00:12:00,737
So in terms of maintaining the balance, it's quite easy.

281
00:12:01,238 --> 00:12:03,201
And every time you want to add a new marble,

282
00:12:03,681 --> 00:12:04,983
if you're data-driven, you might say,

283
00:12:05,704 --> 00:12:07,846
I'm not sure you should add a new marble on this system

284
00:12:07,887 --> 00:12:09,408
because it might create imbalance.

285
00:12:09,969 --> 00:12:11,470
So let me give you a concrete example

286
00:12:11,490 --> 00:12:12,751
of what I'm talking about.

287
00:12:13,231 --> 00:12:15,212
So this is a graph that represents

288
00:12:15,232 --> 00:12:18,874
a win rate between attacker and defender in Rainbow Six Siege.

289
00:12:19,374 --> 00:12:21,536
And since we are an asymmetrical game,

290
00:12:21,896 --> 00:12:23,837
it was really important for us to try to maintain

291
00:12:23,997 --> 00:12:25,258
as much as possible this balance,

292
00:12:25,718 --> 00:12:27,099
because at the beginning of a run,

293
00:12:27,199 --> 00:12:29,700
we want to have each player having a 50-50 chance

294
00:12:29,740 --> 00:12:30,801
to win the run.

295
00:12:31,281 --> 00:12:33,142
And at some point, around August,

296
00:12:33,202 --> 00:12:35,584
you see that we are quite close and quite happy

297
00:12:35,984 --> 00:12:36,744
in terms of balancing.

298
00:12:37,485 --> 00:12:39,406
But at that point, we had another issue in the game.

299
00:12:39,506 --> 00:12:41,067
That was the shotgun.

300
00:12:41,487 --> 00:12:45,389
The shotgun were overwhelmingly good at everything,

301
00:12:46,049 --> 00:12:48,950
from long range to mid range to short range,

302
00:12:48,990 --> 00:12:49,711
good at destruction.

303
00:12:50,191 --> 00:12:51,752
And everyone was using shotgun.

304
00:12:51,892 --> 00:12:54,413
And they were, in terms of diversity, it was like a

