00:21:33,011 --> 00:21:35,572
was winning way more than other people.

515
00:21:35,692 --> 00:21:36,512
This is the win delta.

516
00:21:36,572 --> 00:21:37,273
So the.

517
00:21:38,053 --> 00:21:40,275
increase in win ratio when you have the operator on your team.

518
00:21:40,855 --> 00:21:43,677
And you can see that people realized that this operator was

519
00:21:43,777 --> 00:21:44,277
way too strong.

520
00:21:44,297 --> 00:21:46,359
Like, her pick rate was insane.

521
00:21:46,379 --> 00:21:46,979
It was more than 90%.

522
00:21:48,160 --> 00:21:51,402
She was everywhere, like in Pro League, even in Copper,

523
00:21:51,502 --> 00:21:52,683
in Diamond, like everywhere.

524
00:21:54,044 --> 00:21:55,585
So you know that you have to do something about it.

525
00:21:55,945 --> 00:21:57,927
And on the other hand of the spectrum, we have Tachanka.

526
00:21:57,947 --> 00:21:59,868
So I don't know if you've played the game before,

527
00:21:59,908 --> 00:22:01,969
but this has been a big issue.

528
00:22:04,152 --> 00:22:06,053
Like, some things are easier to balance

529
00:22:06,093 --> 00:22:07,654
because in terms of power levels,

530
00:22:07,914 --> 00:22:09,054
so we're going to talk about that.

531
00:22:09,114 --> 00:22:10,455
But sometimes it's a core mechanic

532
00:22:10,595 --> 00:22:12,536
that you need to change, and it takes more time.

533
00:22:12,576 --> 00:22:14,237
You can adjust both this operator

534
00:22:14,277 --> 00:22:17,299
because he's standing still in a game

535
00:22:17,359 --> 00:22:20,180
where knowing someone's position is crucial

536
00:22:20,821 --> 00:22:22,922
in terms of intelligence and everything.

537
00:22:23,582 --> 00:22:29,586
So, yeah, you need to have bigger production processes

538
00:22:29,626 --> 00:22:30,126
to deal with that.

539
00:22:31,668 --> 00:22:34,711
So once you've seen that, you can then set priorities.

540
00:22:35,772 --> 00:22:37,633
What we try to do, we give a higher priority

541
00:22:37,653 --> 00:22:41,357
in terms of balancing to operators that are overpicked.

542
00:22:41,457 --> 00:22:44,679
Mostly because when you are picked 100% of the time,

543
00:22:45,320 --> 00:22:46,761
when you have five options for your team,

544
00:22:46,821 --> 00:22:49,123
it means that you are taking one of these options

545
00:22:49,323 --> 00:22:52,086
instead of having lots of different situations

546
00:22:52,146 --> 00:22:52,726
that could emerge.

547
00:22:53,487 --> 00:22:55,750
you are fixing your metagame into one situation.

548
00:22:56,411 --> 00:22:57,713
A good example of that is Ella.

549
00:22:58,013 --> 00:22:59,595
So we recently nerfed Ella.

550
00:23:00,056 --> 00:23:03,120
And as you can see, so she is the top pick rate.

551
00:23:03,701 --> 00:23:06,205
And so she went down to the middle of the pack

552
00:23:06,365 --> 00:23:08,107
in terms of pick rate with the latest season.

553
00:23:09,251 --> 00:23:12,093
And sometimes you could have another operator

554
00:23:12,213 --> 00:23:16,136
taking someone's place and becoming the next superstar.

555
00:23:16,156 --> 00:23:20,019
But this time, what we saw is that by bringing Ela more

556
00:23:20,039 --> 00:23:21,801
in line with the other operators,

557
00:23:22,141 --> 00:23:24,102
we gave room for the meta to grow.

558
00:23:24,282 --> 00:23:27,245
Because you could see all the other operators

559
00:23:27,605 --> 00:23:29,206
shifted in terms of pick rates.

560
00:23:29,967 --> 00:23:32,248
And so this challenges the metagame.

561
00:23:32,309 --> 00:23:33,650
This pushes it forward.

562
00:23:34,994 --> 00:23:36,295
So they're trying to take care of that.

563
00:23:36,956 --> 00:23:40,119
Another good thing that is not an absolute truth,

564
00:23:40,159 --> 00:23:43,482
but a good rule of thumb,

565
00:23:43,962 --> 00:23:47,886
is that usually it's easy to fix operators

566
00:23:47,946 --> 00:23:50,388
when their win rates are correlated with the pick rates.

567
00:23:50,929 --> 00:23:53,151
Because it means that either they're good

568
00:23:53,351 --> 00:23:53,951
and people know it.

569
00:23:55,579 --> 00:23:58,580
So they're playing them, or they're bad, and people know it,

570
00:23:58,700 --> 00:23:59,540
and they don't play them.

571
00:23:59,840 --> 00:24:03,721
So by nerfing top pick operators that are winning a lot more,

572
00:24:04,401 --> 00:24:06,962
you're decreasing their attractivity,

573
00:24:07,342 --> 00:24:09,242
and you're bringing them more in line instead of balancing,

574
00:24:09,522 --> 00:24:10,103
and vice versa.

575
00:24:10,783 --> 00:24:12,643
Because if you have an operator that's never picked,

576
00:24:12,843 --> 00:24:15,304
but you buff this one to increase his pick rates,

577
00:24:15,924 --> 00:24:17,904
you just get an operator that is way too strong,

578
00:24:18,044 --> 00:24:19,685
people will notice, and then go straight

579
00:24:19,805 --> 00:24:21,505
to the top right-hand corner.

580
00:24:22,577 --> 00:24:25,598
So by having parameters that you can tweak in terms of weapons,

581
00:24:25,658 --> 00:24:28,759
in terms of gadgets, you can most of the time

582
00:24:28,779 --> 00:24:29,279
do that easily.

583
00:24:29,479 --> 00:24:32,280
So we saw that with LR, which was easier to fix.

584
00:24:32,460 --> 00:24:33,540
But touch and key is another issue.

585
00:24:35,501 --> 00:24:38,221
So the conclusion is that you want to grab those quick wins.

586
00:24:38,641 --> 00:24:40,882
If something is problematic, you see it every time.

587
00:24:40,902 --> 00:24:41,662
People know it's broken.

588
00:24:41,742 --> 00:24:43,543
You have to take care of that as soon as you can.

589
00:24:44,952 --> 00:24:51,014
But don't forget that sometimes you can also give some love to operators that have fallen out of meta

590
00:24:51,414 --> 00:24:57,756
to just like increase their attractivity mixed with the nerfs to like challenge the meta

591
00:24:57,836 --> 00:25:00,537
and make sure that everything is becoming interesting again.

592
00:25:02,197 --> 00:25:04,178
And we have a great example of that.

593
00:25:05,198 --> 00:25:05,578
Blackbeard.

594
00:25:06,535 --> 00:25:08,936
So if you've played the game, Blackbeard

595
00:25:08,956 --> 00:25:12,136
was released during season two, so three months after Frost.

596
00:25:12,836 --> 00:25:16,057
And it was a huge issue when it was released.

597
00:25:16,617 --> 00:25:17,777
So this is where it was at.

598
00:25:18,858 --> 00:25:21,878
So if you remember that, it was the exact same spot.

599
00:25:22,038 --> 00:25:24,939
You're winning all the time, and people know it.

600
00:25:26,399 --> 00:25:29,420
And when you have that, so we had the data,

601
00:25:29,440 --> 00:25:31,120
we had the players feedback, we had everything.

602
00:25:31,140 --> 00:25:32,860
We're like, OK, we need to address Blackbeard.

603
00:25:34,437 --> 00:25:35,498
So cool, thank you.

604
00:25:35,518 --> 00:25:38,160
The data was showing us we needed to act on Blackbeard.

605
00:25:38,200 --> 00:25:40,422
So it was about now to try to find the causes

606
00:25:40,522 --> 00:25:43,625
and validate the causes of what was the issue with Blackbeard.

607
00:25:44,185 --> 00:25:46,187
So to this, we have many processes,

608
00:25:46,207 --> 00:25:48,729
the first one being the qualitative feedback.

609
00:25:49,269 --> 00:25:51,651
As I mentioned, we have a pro player session

610
00:25:52,011 --> 00:25:54,393
that mean people that come to the studio, they play,

611
00:25:54,433 --> 00:25:55,274
and we have focus group.

612
00:25:55,654 --> 00:25:57,135
And since we are focusing on Blackbeard,

613
00:25:57,156 --> 00:25:59,718
because we knew it with data that we need to focus on him,

614
00:26:00,238 --> 00:26:03,179
So it allows us to converge faster on those topics.

615
00:26:03,559 --> 00:26:05,179
We have a pro subreddit.

616
00:26:05,199 --> 00:26:06,640
We even look at Reddit sometimes.

617
00:26:07,100 --> 00:26:09,701
And we have also designer playstations.

618
00:26:10,321 --> 00:26:11,181
We gather together.

619
00:26:11,201 --> 00:26:14,582
We play specifically centered around Blackbeard.

620
00:26:14,882 --> 00:26:18,704
We try to recreate situations and see what was the problem.

621
00:26:19,184 --> 00:26:21,084
And if you know a bit of the game and you know Blackbeard,

622
00:26:21,985 --> 00:26:23,725
it was quite easy to make an hypothesis

623
00:26:23,745 --> 00:26:25,606
about what was the problem.

624
00:26:26,506 --> 00:26:28,088
meet the offender, the shield.

625
00:26:28,288 --> 00:26:29,830
So just to give you a bit of context,

626
00:26:29,990 --> 00:26:34,314
Rainbow Six Siege has a high lethality in terms of gameplay.

627
00:26:34,334 --> 00:26:37,357
That means one bullet from any weapon in your head,

628
00:26:37,498 --> 00:26:40,601
in the head of an enemy, eliminate the enemy

629
00:26:40,961 --> 00:26:42,483
for the duration of the round.

630
00:26:43,730 --> 00:26:48,733
The ability of Blackbeard was to have a ballistic shield on the top of his rifle that was protecting

631
00:26:48,773 --> 00:26:49,113
his head.

632
00:26:49,453 --> 00:26:52,595
So it was making a huge difference in terms of gameplay.

633
00:26:53,135 --> 00:26:58,558
So quickly enough, we were like, probably the shield might be the issue on this one.

634
00:26:59,058 --> 00:27:00,839
So it was just a hypothesis.

635
00:27:00,979 --> 00:27:06,282
Then we go back to Geoffroy and ask him, OK, can you look at the data and see if there

636
00:27:06,402 --> 00:27:09,844
is a correlation between the shield being an issue and something in the data.

637
00:27:10,444 --> 00:27:11,905
And they come back with a lot of data

638
00:27:12,045 --> 00:27:15,606
and it was quickly clear that just with a kill-death ratio,

639
00:27:15,626 --> 00:27:17,927
for example, that Blackbeard was killing more

640
00:27:18,107 --> 00:27:20,068
than he was dying.

641
00:27:20,469 --> 00:27:23,490
So clearly, on operators, that was too safe.

642
00:27:23,910 --> 00:27:27,091
So, okay, and I just say, go work on the shield.

643
00:27:28,118 --> 00:27:30,379
So now, I will explain you this story,

644
00:27:30,399 --> 00:27:31,600
because it's really interesting, because you

645
00:27:31,620 --> 00:27:34,162
will see that it's a two-step solution.

646
00:27:34,622 --> 00:27:37,064
Because at that time, we knew that we had the problem,

647
00:27:37,144 --> 00:27:38,805
and we knew we had to work on the shield.

648
00:27:39,505 --> 00:27:43,208
But at that time, we didn't have the kind of process

649
00:27:43,228 --> 00:27:43,968
that we have right now.

650
00:27:44,308 --> 00:27:46,730
That means the analysts were still on one side of the team,

651
00:27:46,750 --> 00:27:47,630
like far away.

652
00:27:47,991 --> 00:27:50,372
They send us info about Blackbeard, about the shield.

653
00:27:50,752 --> 00:27:52,594
But then we came back a designer,

654
00:27:52,694 --> 00:27:55,115
on our room of designers, working on the solution

655
00:27:55,155 --> 00:27:55,976
and the implementation.

656
00:27:56,416 --> 00:27:58,457
So I'm like, OK, guys, let's act on the shield.

657
00:27:58,557 --> 00:27:59,597
And we make a change.

658
00:27:59,757 --> 00:28:00,918
The shield was destructible.

659
00:28:01,438 --> 00:28:04,419
At the beginning, he had 800 HP.

660
00:28:04,799 --> 00:28:08,220
So we decided to change that to make it 150 HP

661
00:28:08,460 --> 00:28:11,341
and add a second shield.

662
00:28:11,461 --> 00:28:12,742
So you could have a second shield.

663
00:28:13,042 --> 00:28:13,902
That means overall 300 HP.

664
00:28:15,623 --> 00:28:18,445
but 150 HP per shield.

665
00:28:18,845 --> 00:28:22,487
And it creates a nice mechanism of resource management.

666
00:28:22,647 --> 00:28:24,068
And since it was the only ability,

667
00:28:24,489 --> 00:28:27,350
we felt a bit bad to just nerf him down to this point.

668
00:28:27,831 --> 00:28:29,532
And so we make that.

669
00:28:29,652 --> 00:28:30,853
We believe it's interesting.

670
00:28:31,173 --> 00:28:32,254
We make some PlayStation.

671
00:28:32,274 --> 00:28:33,715
We discuss with pro and stuff like that.

672
00:28:33,755 --> 00:28:34,175
We play it.

673
00:28:34,195 --> 00:28:35,035
And we're like, that's good.

674
00:28:35,055 --> 00:28:35,356
That's good.

675
00:28:35,916 --> 00:28:37,317
We were even like, pfff.

676
00:28:38,077 --> 00:28:40,319
Maybe it's too big as a nerf.

677
00:28:40,339 --> 00:28:43,722
Like maybe we might have put him in an underwhelming position.

678
00:28:43,823 --> 00:28:46,745
But you know, at that point, it was the biggest issue

679
00:28:46,785 --> 00:28:47,746
we ever had in the game.

680
00:28:48,167 --> 00:28:50,469
So we were like, we need to strike hard to show

681
00:28:50,489 --> 00:28:51,810
that we care about the meta.

682
00:28:52,210 --> 00:28:54,753
And there is no overpowered character under our reign.

683
00:28:55,253 --> 00:28:57,475
So confident enough, we push those changes.

684
00:28:58,136 --> 00:28:59,016
And we look at the data.

685
00:29:01,369 --> 00:29:02,010
And nothing changed.

686
00:29:02,830 --> 00:29:04,331
Like, literally, nothing changed.

687
00:29:04,731 --> 00:29:06,672
It was way above the other operator,

688
00:29:06,872 --> 00:29:08,533
and we were like, oh, wow.

689
00:29:09,334 --> 00:29:10,635
So, wow.

690
00:29:10,995 --> 00:29:13,076
So we came back to our analyst friend,

691
00:29:13,136 --> 00:29:15,838
and we were like, okay, so we validated

692
00:29:15,878 --> 00:29:16,798
that it was a problem.

693
00:29:16,939 --> 00:29:18,419
We validated that it was a shield issue.

694
00:29:18,960 --> 00:29:21,041
We nerved down the shield like, hey, insane.

695
00:29:21,061 --> 00:29:23,162
We even took some clash from the community

696
00:29:23,202 --> 00:29:24,203
and stuff like that for doing so.

697
00:29:25,144 --> 00:29:27,045
And the guy is still like super overpowered.

698
00:29:27,065 --> 00:29:28,726
So guys, we need your help on this point

699
00:29:28,746 --> 00:29:30,907
because we don't really understand what is going on.

700
00:29:32,332 --> 00:29:35,820
Yeah, and so at the time, we were super happy,

701
00:29:35,840 --> 00:29:37,885
because having designers coming to your desk being like,

702
00:29:37,985 --> 00:29:39,789
oh my god, maybe he loves me or something.

703
00:29:41,281 --> 00:29:45,983
And so we were like, but we can actually help you,

704
00:29:46,024 --> 00:29:48,125
because we have lots of data about Blackbeard.

705
00:29:48,145 --> 00:29:51,826
Like Kirill said, we had information about kill, death,

706
00:29:51,886 --> 00:29:54,028
but more especially about the shield.

707
00:29:54,108 --> 00:29:57,609
Like we knew how much damage the shields would receive,

708
00:29:58,970 --> 00:30:01,471
how many times it would be destroyed and everything.

709
00:30:01,571 --> 00:30:03,492
So just by looking at the data, we

710
00:30:03,532 --> 00:30:05,853
saw that with the new shield that was supposed

711
00:30:05,913 --> 00:30:07,594
to have a low amount of HP.

712
00:30:08,895 --> 00:30:11,737
it would break like one round out of 20.

713
00:30:11,797 --> 00:30:15,238
So it's like, OK, basically it's not working.

714
00:30:15,298 --> 00:30:18,019
It makes perfect sense that nothing changes,

715
00:30:19,380 --> 00:30:22,401
because, well, it's still heavily protected.

716
00:30:23,701 --> 00:30:25,462
And so what it is that, well, actually we

717
00:30:25,482 --> 00:30:27,203
have the data about the damage distribution.

718
00:30:27,543 --> 00:30:31,384
So we can look at how much damage the shield would receive.

719
00:30:31,945 --> 00:30:34,746
And if you want to set a percentage of.

720
00:30:35,788 --> 00:30:37,948
the times the shield should be destroyed, we can do it.

721
00:30:38,789 --> 00:30:40,509
So what we did is that we asked them.

722
00:30:40,529 --> 00:30:42,210
They wanted to have about a third of the time

723
00:30:43,090 --> 00:30:43,910
the shield to be destroyed.

724
00:30:44,550 --> 00:30:47,251
So we just did a basic model trying

725
00:30:47,311 --> 00:30:49,471
to add two distributions for the two shields,

726
00:30:49,551 --> 00:30:50,892
depending on whether they were used or not,

727
00:30:51,472 --> 00:30:56,773
to see if we put this threshold of damage at this level,

728
00:30:56,813 --> 00:30:59,114
then this percentage of shields would break.

729
00:31:00,298 --> 00:31:00,998
This is what we did.

730
00:31:01,518 --> 00:31:04,499
We came back to the design team saying, hey, we've solved it.

731
00:31:04,699 --> 00:31:06,019
And so you should put it down to 60.

732
00:31:07,379 --> 00:31:09,860
And Lira's reaction at the time was like, no way.

733
00:31:10,380 --> 00:31:12,140
This is just insane.

734
00:31:12,160 --> 00:31:15,321
You could just put a piece of paper on that trifle,

735
00:31:15,341 --> 00:31:16,301
and that would do the same thing.

736
00:31:16,981 --> 00:31:20,082
That's two to three bullets at most.

737
00:31:20,162 --> 00:31:23,402
But we're like, guys, we do math.

738
00:31:23,722 --> 00:31:25,803
We are pretty confident about this.

739
00:31:28,063 --> 00:31:29,743
And so luckily enough, this guy didn't.

740
00:31:29,844 --> 00:31:32,345
So they're like, OK, I guess maybe you're right.

741
00:31:32,725 --> 00:31:34,266
And so they trusted us on this.

742
00:31:34,526 --> 00:31:36,367
And then they patched it.

743
00:31:36,567 --> 00:31:39,128
And the community's reaction was exactly the same.

744
00:31:39,629 --> 00:31:41,830
Like, everyone was like, this is the biggest

745
00:31:41,910 --> 00:31:43,170
nerf in the history of Siege.

746
00:31:43,511 --> 00:31:44,971
Like, this character is useless.

747
00:31:45,011 --> 00:31:48,613
Like, nobody will play Nerf Beard ever again.

748
00:31:49,334 --> 00:31:52,239
And so we had like memes for months and months after that.

749
00:31:52,800 --> 00:32:00,131
Except that we did the change and actually it finally brought Blackbeard back in line with the other operators.

750
00:32:01,766 --> 00:32:03,047
He was still good.

751
00:32:03,667 --> 00:32:06,049
Like, he was still one of the top faggots of the game,

752
00:32:06,169 --> 00:32:07,970
which is like what he's supposed to do,

753
00:32:08,010 --> 00:32:09,871
because that's what his gadget does.

754
00:32:10,651 --> 00:32:12,733
But like, he was actually a good operator.

755
00:32:12,833 --> 00:32:15,514
And it took months for the community to figure that out.

756
00:32:15,655 --> 00:32:18,336
So the pick rate went down to 2% or 3%,

757
00:32:18,977 --> 00:32:21,478
and slowly went back up to the point

758
00:32:21,498 --> 00:32:25,481
where today it's now played in Pro League at the top level.

759
00:32:26,667 --> 00:32:28,769
He's even considered one of the best operators in the game.

760
00:32:29,469 --> 00:32:31,871
And except for maybe one change on one of these here,

761
00:32:32,111 --> 00:32:34,753
nothing changed since we nerfed it for the first time.

762
00:32:35,813 --> 00:32:38,955
So just by trying to get your data more carefully

763
00:32:39,015 --> 00:32:41,057
and trying to work together, trying to find solutions

764
00:32:41,177 --> 00:32:45,480
and how to fix them using data smartly,

765
00:32:45,940 --> 00:32:47,181
you can do great things for your game.

766
00:32:47,381 --> 00:32:50,003
Even if it's counterintuitive, even if you're

